<p>The four suits of the Tarot pack, discussed by Jessie
        Weston in From Ritual to Romance, are the cup, lance,
        sword, and dish - the life symbols found in the Grail
        story. Weston noted that "today the Tarot has fallen
        somewhat into disrepute, being principally used for
        purposes of divination." (NA) </p>
